Get a canonical service name for this file system. The token cache is the only user of the canonical service name, and uses it to lookup this filesystem's service tokens. If file system provides a token of its own then it must have a canonical name, otherwise canonical name can be null.
Default Impl: If the file system has child file systems (such as an embedded file system) then it is assumed that the fs has no tokens of its own and hence returns a null name; otherwise a service name is built using Uri and port.
@return a service string that uniquely identifies this file system, null if the filesystem does not implement tokens @see SecurityUtil#buildDTServiceName(URI, int)

